OF ALL THEIR WEALTH.

83
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:55,916
SUCH TRAGEDY IS RIFE THESE DAYS.

84
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,916
- MAGISTRATES? I SEE.

85
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,625
THE GUYS BACK HOME
USED TO TALK.

86
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:04,000
THEY'D SAY THE SAME THING.
EVER SINCE THE CURRENT EMPEROR

87
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:05,625
PARKED HIS RUMP IN THE THRONE,

88
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,708
THEY SAY IT'S GOTTEN WORSE.

89
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:10,958
NOT JUST IN TOWNS LIKE THIS,
BUT EVERYWHERE.

90
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:14,375
DAMN IT. BETWEEN MOUSTACHE
AND WELL, WHOEVER IS RUNNING

91
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:16,791
THE SHOW HERE, IT'S A TRAVESTY.

92
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:19,250
THE EMPIRE IS NOTHING
BUT A BUNCH OF FAT...

93
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,666
- SHUT UP. YOU TRYING
TO GET US ARRESTED?

94
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,041
- TELL YOU WHAT.
SINCE WE'RE HERE,

95
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:25,250
I'LL GO PROCURE LODGINGS
FOR THE NIGHT.

96
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:28,083
AND YOU TWO CAN TAKE
A LITTLE TOUR OF THAT BIG SHIP.

97
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,708
- I'M SURE THEY'D WELCOME
THE CURIOUS.

98
00:06:29,791 --> 00:06:30,916
- NOW YOU'RE TALKING.

99
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,208
- HOW DO YOU ALWAYS KNOW
JUST WHAT TO SAY?

100
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:34,458
- SEE YOU IN A BIT.

101
00:06:34,541 --> 00:06:35,958
- ABSOLUTELY NOT.

102
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:39,125
- CAN'T YOU MAKE AN EXCEPTION
FOR US? COME ON, PLEASE.

103
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:41,250
WE JUST WANT TO HAVE
A LITTLE PEEK INSIDE.

104
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:44,458
- THIS IS THE DOU YA, KID.
NOT SOME FLOATING MUSEUM.

105
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,458
THE WO JIN SQUAD
DOESN'T PLAY TOUR GUIDE

106
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:47,916
TO SNOT-NOSED COMMONERS.

107
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,708
- WHO ARE YOU CALLING
A SNOT-NOSED COMMONER,

108
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:51,125
YOU ONE-EYED RIVER RAT?

109
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:53,500
- COME ON, LET US ON BOARD.
- TAITO.

110
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,583
- ( coughs )

111
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:02,458
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
IS IT TOO COLD OUT FOR YOU?

112
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:04,958
DEAR SISTER, CURSE THIS
INCURABLE DISEASE

113
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:06,291
LAYING WASTE TO YOU.

114
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:10,375
- ( coughs ) BROTHER, I HAVE
BUT ONE WISH BEFORE

115
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:12,541
THE DISEASE CLAIMS
ITS FINAL TOLL.

116
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:14,666
- SPEAK IT ALOUD, DEAR SISTER.

117
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:18,250
- WHILE I, WHILE I STILL
POSSESS THE STRENGTH TO STAND,

118
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,916
I WISH TO BOARD THIS SHIP.

119
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,375
- OF COURSE. ANYTHING
AT ALL FOR MY DEAR SISTER.

120
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:27,291
SURELY, THIS KIND SAILOR'S
HEART CANNOT BE MADE OF STONE.

121
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:28,791
- WELL THEN, HOW ABOUT IT?

122
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:32,083
YOU GOING TO LET US ON?
- GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

123
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:35,041
- WHAT A JERK.
YELLING AT A SICK GIRL.

124
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,625
- I'M KINDA SHOCKED, ACTUALLY.

125
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:38,500
THAT WAS A ONCE IN A LIFETIME
PERFORMANCE.

126
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,750
- AH, THERE YOU ARE.
- HUH?

127
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:42,541
- I FOUND A PLACE FOR US
TO STAY.

128
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,750
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

129
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,000
- NOT TO NITPICK,

130
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:49,791
BUT, UH, THIS PLACE LOOKS
A LITTLE RUN-DOWN.

131
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:52,250
- THAT IT IS. BUT FOR
OUR HUMBLE PURPOSE,

132
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,916
IT WILL MORE THAN SUFFICE.

133
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,000
- YOU AGAIN? WHAT DO YOU WANT?

134
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,291
- YES, MA'AM.

135
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:02,083
THESE TWO ARE MY FRIENDS.
THE ONES I SPOKE TO YOU ABOUT.

136
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:04,916
WE SEEK SHELTER FOR THE EVENING.

137
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:09,250
- I SUPPOSE. THE RAIN
WILL BRING A CHILL.

138
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:12,625
I'LL MUSTER UP SOME EXTRA
BLANKETS FOR YOU. SOMEWHERE.

139
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:16,708
- WE'RE GRATEFUL TO YOU.

140
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:20,583
- WELL, UH, SHE SEEMS NICE.
- YEAH, REAL NICE.

141
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:31,000
- Oen: IMAGINE ME, SHARING
MY TABLE WITH NONE OTHER THAN

142
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:33,875
KOYO OF THE WO JIN SQUAD.

143
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,166
PRESIDING OVER
A HOLE IN THE GROUND

144
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:36,625
LIKE THIS DOES HAVE ITS PERKS.

145
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:38,583
FEW AND FAR BETWEEN AS THEY ARE.

146
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,458
- ( people chattering )

147
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:41,958
- ( chuckles ) YOU FLATTER ME.

148
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:44,708
THE FACT OF THE MATTER IS,
IF I MAY SPEAK CANDIDLY, SIR,

149
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:46,875
IF I'D HAVE KNOWN
YOU WERE POISED TO RETURN,

150
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,250
I'D HAVE COME SOONER.

151
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:51,000
THE CAPITAL'S IN NEED
OF SHREWD MEN LIKE YOURSELF.

152
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:53,500
- ( chuckles ) WELL PLAYED.

153
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:55,416
THAT SAME SILVER TONGUE
MUST'VE MANEUVERED YOU

154
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,291
INTO THE POSITION OF CAPTAIN.

155
00:08:57,375 --> 00:09:00,708
- I THINK YOU FLATTER ME.
- NOT ONE BIT, SIR.

156
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:04,000
- WE LOWLY ENTREPRENEURS MAKE
IT A POINT OF READING THE TIDE.

157
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:05,708
THAT'S HOW WE STAY AFLOAT.

158
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:08,750
I HOPE IT'S NOT VULGAR OF ME
TO SAY, BUT WHEN ALL SIGNS

159
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,625
POINT TO A MILITARY COUP,

160
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:13,708
