TO WORK THAT OUT FOR YOURSELF.

210
00:11:27,125 --> 00:11:31,041
- ALL RIGHT THEN.
LET'S DO THIS.

211
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:36,500
- YOU'VE ALREADY USED
CHANNELING ONCE, TAITO.

212
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:38,291
WHETHER YOU KNOW IT OR NOT.

213
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:40,916
DO I DARE RISK RE-AWAKENING
ALKAID BY TEACHING YOU

214
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,875
HOW TO USE IT CONSCIOUSLY?

215
00:11:42,958 --> 00:11:46,208
MAY THE STARS GUIDE US.
THEIR WAY IS OUR WAY.

216
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,041
- WOW, LOOK AT ALL
OF THEM.

217
00:11:58,125 --> 00:12:00,416
SOLDIERS AS FAR
AS THE EYE CAN SEE.

218
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:04,250
WAVE AFTER WAVE. LED BY
THE BIG MAN HIMSELF, NO LESS.

219
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:06,625
THE ONE WHO IS SITTING PRETTY
WHILE HIS MEN TOUGH IT OUT

220
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:08,583
HERE IN THE WILDERNESS.

221
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:11,083
( whimpers ) THESE POUR SOULS.

222
00:12:11,166 --> 00:12:13,500
( chuckles ) LET'S GO SEE
IF I CAN LIGHTEN THEIR LOAD.

223
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:19,083
- ( snoring )

224
00:12:19,166 --> 00:12:21,541
- TAITO, WAKE UP. WAKE UP

225
00:12:23,125 --> 00:12:28,208
- ( grunts ) I SAID WAKE UP!
- Taito: OW.

226
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:30,125
- SO, NOW, WE ARE
STRANDED HERE. GREAT.

227
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,458
- THE FLOODING'S BOUND
TO SUBSIDE BEFORE TOO LONG.

228
00:12:32,541 --> 00:12:34,875
THERE'S NOTHING TO DO BUT WAIT.
TRY TO MAKE THE MOST OF IT.

229
00:12:36,625 --> 00:12:38,750
- YEAH, I GUESS.

230
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,166
HEY, AT LEAST THIS GIVES ME
A CHANCE TO GET SOME MORE

231
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,500
TRAINING UNDER MY BELT, RIGHT?

232
00:12:41,583 --> 00:12:43,541
- HA. TRAINING FOR WHAT,
I'D LIKE TO KNOW.

233
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:44,875
SLEEPING IN ALL DAY?

234
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:46,458
- THAT'S ABOUT ALL
YOU'VE DONE SO FAR.

235
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:47,875
- SHUT YOUR FACE!

236
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:49,583
- HMM.
- HMM.

237
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:52,208
- EXCUSE ME FOR JUST A MOMENT.

238
00:12:52,291 --> 00:12:53,500
- IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT,
MA'AM?

239
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:55,333
IS THERE ANYTHING
WE CAN DO?

240
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:57,041
- NO, NO. YOU'RE FINE.

241
00:12:57,125 --> 00:12:59,750
THIS ROOM IS WHERE I HAVE
THE BEST VIEW, THAT'S ALL.

242
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:07,750
FORGIVE MY POOR MANNERS.

243
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,458
I'LL BET YOU'D LIKE ME TO BRING
IN SOME MORE TEA, WOULDN'T YOU?

244
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:11,875
- AH. YES PLEASE.

245
00:13:14,708 --> 00:13:16,875
- WE CALL HIM THE SACRED BEAR.

246
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:19,500
HE IS THE VILLAGE'S
GUARDIAN SPIRIT.

247
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:24,708
FOR UNTOLD GENERATIONS,
HE HAS PROTECTED US.

248
00:13:24,791 --> 00:13:27,041
WE'VE WORSHIPED HIM
SINCE TIME OUT OF MIND

249
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:30,833
AND GLADLY, HIS BENEVOLENCE
HAS BEEN OUR BOON.

250
00:13:30,916 --> 00:13:34,000
BUT AS OF LATE, CORRUPT
OFFICIALS LIKE OUR LATEST

251
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:35,541
BLOCKHEADED LORD MAYOR

252
00:13:35,625 --> 00:13:38,833
FORBID US FROM PAYING HOMAGE
TO ANYTHING BUT WHAT THE EMPIRE

253
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:39,875
DEEMS APPROPRIATE.

254
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:41,791
- REALLY?

255
00:13:41,875 --> 00:13:43,958
- POOR AS WE ARE, IN ORDER
TO SURVIVE AT ALL,

256
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:45,708
WE MUST DO
AS WE'RE TOLD.

257
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:49,083
WE'VE HAD TO SURRENDER
OUR FAITH.

258
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:51,208
- THAT'S WRONG. IT'S CRUEL.

259
00:13:51,291 --> 00:13:53,291
YOU GUYS SHOULD ALL BAND
TOGETHER AND KICK THE MAYOR OUT.

260
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:55,458
STAND UP AND FIGHT.

261
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:58,708
- Man: OPEN UP.
WE'VE GOT AN EMERGENCY.

262
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:02,375
- THAT IS UNTHINKABLE.
YOU MEN. PREPOSTEROUS.

263
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,333
THE SACRED BEAR HAS STOOD
FOR CENTURIES.

264
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:06,125
IT'S NOT GOING TO COME
CRASHING DOWN NOW

265
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:07,333
ON ACCOUNT OF A LITTLE RAIN.

266
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:09,083
- THERE'S NO POINT IN DENYING
IT ANYMORE.

267
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:11,166
THAT ROCK IS
TEETERING ON THE BRINK.

268
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,083
THE TOWN IS IN JEOPARDY.

269
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:14,833
- WORSE YET, THE ROADS
ARE FLOODED.

270
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:16,666
WE HAVE NO
OPTION BUT TO STAY HERE.

271
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:19,125
- PERHAPS, THIS IS NO MORE
THAN WE DESERVE FOR HAVING

272
00:14:19,208 --> 00:14:20,958
ABANDONED OUR GUARDIAN.

273
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:22,458
- WHAT'LL WE DO?

274
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,125
- THERE'S NOTHING
TO DO BUT FLEE.

275
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:25,000
WE'LL TAKE OUR CHANCES.

276
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:26,708
THIS TOWN'S FATE IS NOT OURS.

277
00:14:26,791 --> 00:14:29,166
- WE CAN'T JUST LEAVE
THESE POOR PEOPLE TO BE CRUSHED.

278
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:31,666
- WE'RE NOT LEAVING THEM.
THEY NEED OUR HELP.

279
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,666
I DON'T GIVE A
DAMN ABOUT FATE.

280
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,166
AH, I'VE GOT AN IDEA.

281
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:38,333
- IT'S A MATTER OF LIFE
AND DEATH.

282
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:39,458
- WE BEG YOU.

283
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:41,000
- I TOLD YOU THE ANSWER IS NO.

284
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:43,208
I DON'T CARE IF THAT ROCK
SPROUTS LEGS AND WALKS.

285
00:14:43,291 --> 00:14:45,375
THEY'RE NOT SETTING FOOT
ON THIS SHIP AND THAT'S FINAL.

286
00:14:45,458 --> 00:14:47,708
- SCREW YOU.
I DEMAND TO SEE THE CAPTAIN.

287
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:49,708
- PLEASE, JUST LET US
TALK TO HIM.

288
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,000
- GIVE ME A BREAK.

289
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:52,500
I'M NOT GOING TO PESTER
THE BOSS FOR YOU TWO.

290
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:55,291
NOW, GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE
BEFORE I START TO GET MAD.

291
00:14:55,375 --> 00:14:57,708
- AH, YOU SON OF A...

292
00:14:57,791 --> 00:14:58,916
- ( grunts )

293
00:15:02,458 --> 00:15:03,833
- YOU LITTLE PUNK.

294
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:06,000
- I DON'T HAVE TIME TO DEAL
WITH PISSANTS LIKE YOU.

295
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:07,875
GET YOUR CAPTAIN
OUT HERE RIGHT NOW.

296
00:15:07,958 --> 00:15:09,333
- WHO ARE YOU
TO BARK ORDERS AT US?

297
00:15:09,416 --> 00:15:11,458
- WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE PROBLEM?

298
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,625
THREE AGAINST ONE STRIKE
YOU FELLAS AS THE BEST WAY

299
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:15,000
TO REPRESENT THE WO JIN SQUAD?

300
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:16,791
- THIS KID'S THE ONE
THAT THREW THE FIRST PUNCH.

301
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:18,750
- DO I HAVE TO SPELL IT OUT?

302
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:23,250
- SO, I GUESS YOU ARE
THE CAPTAIN OF THIS RIG, HUH?

303
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,500
- NAME'S KOYO. AND YOU ARE?

304
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:28,625
- MY NAME'S TAITO.
WE'VE GOT A PROBLEM.

305
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:31,416
THAT BOULDER UP THERE
IS GOING TO FALL ANY MINUTE.

306
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,833
NOW LOOK. THE PEOPLE HAVE
NO WAY OUT.

307
00:15:33,916 --> 00:15:35,958
THEY'LL ALL BE KILLED.
LET THEM ON BOARD.

308
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,083
- PLEASE, SIR.
WE'LL DO ANYTHING.

309
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:39,500
- Oen: CLEAR A PATH.

310
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,666
SORRY TO MAKE YOU WAIT, CAPTAIN.

311
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,875
- NOT AT ALL, LORD MAYOR.

312
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:49,208
YOUR APPEARANCE
IS IMPECCABLY TIMED.

313
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:52,375
- HMM. BELIEVE ME, MY FRIEND,
YOU DON'T KNOW THE HALF OF IT.

314
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:54,416
THAT TREASURE'S NOT
GOING TO HAUL ITSELF.

315
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,291
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?
CHOP CHOP, WASTRELS.

316
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:01,583
- MY GOOD MAN, WE GREATLY
APPRECIATE THE ASSISTANCE.

317
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:04,000
- DON'T THINK WE WILL FORGET
YOU IN THE DAYS TO COME.

318
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:06,458
- YOUR GRATITUDE HONORS ME.
THANK YOU, SIR.

319
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:10,875
- HEY, HOLD ON.
WHAT ABOUT EVERYBODY ELSE?

320
00:16:10,958 --> 00:16:13,708
ISN'T A POOR PERSON'S
GRATITUDE ENOUGH FOR YOU?

321
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:17,333
- OH, WHAT A WIT. WHO'S THE
RUNT? NOT ONE OF YOURS I HOPE.

322
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:20,208
- NO, SIR. HE MISTAKES ME
FOR A PHILANTHROPIST

323
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:22,750
AND EXPECTS MY SHIP
TO HARBOR THE ENTIRE TOWN.

324
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:25,250
- DON'T BE ABSURD.
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

325
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:27,291
I'M NOT SHARING QUARTERS
WITH PEASANTS.

326
00:16:27,375 --> 00:16:29,375
THE RABBLE WILL JUST
HAVE TO FEND FOR THEMSELVES.

327
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:30,791
IT'S NONE OF MY CONCERN.

328
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:32,166
- YOU HEARTLESS MONSTER.

329
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,583
- LOOK AT IT THIS WAY.

330
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:35,708
THEY'VE HELD THE OLD FAITH
SECRETLY ALL THESE YEARS.

331
00:16:35,791 --> 00:16:37,333
MAYBE THEIR GOD
WILL SPARE THEM.

332
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:38,958
( laughs )

333
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:45,750
- TAITO, WAIT.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

334
00:16:48,416 --> 00:16:50,458
- ( laughs )

335
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:51,875
BEHOLD THE SECRET
KINGS OF MEN.

336
00:16:51,958 --> 00:16:54,375
I'VE SPENT AN AGE BUILDING
THIS LITTLE NEST EGG.

337
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:56,750
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
WHO HEDGES HIS BETS.

338
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:59,541
- I CAN TELL BUT SURELY
THIS CAN'T BE ALL.

339
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:02,625
THAT IS, I'D EXPECTED TO SEE
THE JEWEL OF THE SACRED BEAR.

340
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:04,791
- JEWEL OF THE SACRED BEAR?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

341
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:07,333
- WELL, SIR.
ACCORDING TO MY INFORMATION,

342
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:10,041
THE JEWEL SAID TO HAVE BEEN
BURIED BY YOUR PREDECESSOR,

343
00:17:10,125 --> 00:17:12,125
IS ONE OF THE LARGEST
IN THE REALM.

344
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:13,708
DON'T TELL ME IT'S NOT HERE.

345
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:17,000
I ASSUMED YOUR MEN WOULD
HAVE DISCOVERED IT BY NOW.

346
00:17:17,083 --> 00:17:19,166
- HURRY IT UP, CRETINS!

347
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:22,291
- MY WORD. THAT KOYO
IS WORTH HIS WEIGHT IN GOLD.

348
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:25,208
- I'LL SAY. A GEM OF THAT
CALIBER HAS BEEN UNDER

349
00:17:25,291 --> 00:17:26,791
OUR FEET THIS WHOLE TIME?

350
00:17:26,875 --> 00:17:30,708
JUST WHAT I NEED TO SECURE
MY FORTUNES.

351
00:17:30,791 --> 00:17:32,541
- THE OLD BEAR IS NOT
GOING TO HOLD MUCH LONGER

352
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,375
IN THIS DOWNPOUR.

353
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:38,625
HEY, YOU THERE, GIRL.
THE VIEW'S FAR BETTER ON BOARD.

354
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:46,458
- THIS IS A LOAD OF CRAP.

355
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:49,541
POOR PEOPLE HAVE TO DIE JUST
SO RICH BASTARDS LIKE HIM,

356
00:17:49,625 --> 00:17:51,625
CAN CLEAR OUT WITH EVERYTHING?

357
00:17:51,708 --> 00:17:54,916
WELL, NOT ON MY WATCH.

358
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,708
TRY TO HOLD ON, OKAY?
JUST A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

359
00:17:57,791 --> 00:17:59,541
GIVE YOUR PEOPLE A CHANCE
TO ESCAPE.

360
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:03,083
HOLD ON, DAMN IT!

361
00:18:05,166 --> 00:18:07,833
- YOU KNOW, TAITO.
I FEEL FOR YOUR SISTER.

362
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:10,583
- SHE'S GROWN UP HAVING TO DEAL
WITH THIS KIND OF STUPIDITY.

363
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:12,000
- RYUKO.

364
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:14,625
- AS MASTER SONNEI SAYS,
NO ONE FORGES THEIR PATH ALONE.

365
00:18:14,708 --> 00:18:16,041
THOUGH YOU CAN BELIEVE
AS YOU LIKE.

366
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:19,916
- PUT YOUR BACKS INTO IT, MEN.

367
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,583
WHOEVER FINDS THE JEWEL,
GETS A PROMOTION.

368
00:18:22,666 --> 00:18:25,208
WE'RE GETTING CLOSE.
SO CLOSE I CAN TASTE IT.

369
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:27,458
( laughs )

370
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:32,083
- HAVE YOU GOT IT YET OR WHAT?
- DONE. YOU CAN LET GO NOW.

371
00:18:32,166 --> 00:18:34,500
- I DO BELIEVE THAT
WILL HOLD QUITE NICELY.

372
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:37,916
THEN AGAIN, IF THIS RAIN
SOFTENS THE GROUND ANY MORE,

373
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,333
WHO KNOWS?

374
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:41,791
- AH.
- RYUKO!

375
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,541
- WHA... WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

376
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:53,875
- ( grunts )

377
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:57,041
- LET GO OF ME. THERE IS
NO POINT IN BOTH OF US FALLING.

378
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:58,416
I'LL BE FINE, TRUST ME.

379
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:01,000
- YEAH, NICE TRY. I DON'T
CARE HOW STRONG YOU ARE.

380
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:02,166
A FALL FROM THIS
KIND OF HEIGHT?

381
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,208
PLEASE, THERE'S NO WAY
YOU'D SURVIVE IT.

382
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:07,125
- TAITO, NEITHER ONE OF US
WILL SURVIVE IF YOU DON'T.

383
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:11,541
LET GO OF MY ARM. LET GO!

384
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,625
DAMN IT, DO AS I TELL YOU.

385
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:15,208
- THAT'S NOT GOING TO HAPPEN.

386
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,500
YOU MADE A PROMISE TO COME
WITH ME TO THE CAPITAL

387
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,083
AND I'M GOING TO HOLD YOU TO IT.

388
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:23,166
YOU'RE NOT JUST MY CUSTODIAN,
YOU'RE MY FRIEND.

389
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:24,916
WHAT WAS ALL THAT CRAP
ABOUT NONE OF US

390
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,250
BEING ALONE IN THIS, HUH?

391
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,208
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO COME
HELP ME SAVE THESE PEOPLE

392
00:19:28,291 --> 00:19:30,375
OR EVEN COME WITH ME ON THIS
JOURNEY IN THE FIRST PLACE

393
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:33,583
BUT WE'RE IN THIS TOGETHER NOW.
I'M NOT GOING TO LET GO!

394
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,125
- TAITO.

395
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:39,875
THE ALKAID SIGIL.

396
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:41,833
- ( screams )

397
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:49,750
- ( panting )

398
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,125
- YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

399
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:57,166
- YEAH, WELL,
WHAT ARE FRIENDS FOR?

400
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,416
- ( thunder rumbling )

401
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:13,083
- THE BOULDER!
- OUR SACRED BEAR.

402
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:15,958
- MY LORD, THE ROCK!
- WHAT?

403
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:17,250
- ( people screaming )

404
00:20:32,166 --> 00:20:34,791
- I'M SORRY. WE REALLY
TRIED TO SAVE THIS PLACE.

405
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:38,041
- DON'T BE DAFT.
THE THREE OF YOU ARE HEROES.

406
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:40,666
ROADS AND BUILDINGS
ARE EASY TO REPLACE.

407
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:43,708
WHAT'S IMPORTANT IS THAT
LIVES HAVE BEEN SPARED.

408
00:20:43,791 --> 00:20:45,000
AND FROM NOW ON,

409
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:49,500
OUR BELOVED GUARDIAN
IS THAT MUCH NEARER TO US.

410
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:52,416
- THAT CAPTAIN, WHY DID HE
SUDDENLY DECIDE TO HELP?

411
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:56,041
- I MEAN, HE SEEMED LIKE
SUCH A MEAN GUY AT FIRST.

412
00:20:56,125 --> 00:21:00,416
- I DON'T KNOW.

413
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,250
- ( laughs )

414
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,250
I ALMOST FEEL SORRY
FOR THE MAN, FALLING FOR

415
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,916
SUCH AN OBVIOUS CHARADE.

416
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,125
JUST GOES TO SHOW YOU
HOW FAR GREED CLOUDS THE MIND.

417
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:12,250
- I MUST SAY, THOUGH,
COMING OUT HERE WAS CERTAINLY

418
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:13,291
PROFITABLE FOR US.

419
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:15,083
TOO BAD FOR THE TOWN.

420
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:16,333
I NEVER WOULD HAVE EXPECTED
THE SACRED BEAR

421
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:17,791
TO COME DOWN SO SOON.

422
00:21:17,875 --> 00:21:19,708
- OH, WELL,
HE WHO MOVES MOUNTAINS

423
00:21:19,791 --> 00:21:21,583
MOVES THEM STONE BY STONE.

424
00:21:21,666 --> 00:21:25,250
THE BOY, TAITO. I'LL HAVE
TO REMEMBER THAT NAME.

425
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,583
- FINALLY, MAN. I WAS STARTING
TO THINK WE'D NEVER GET BACK

426
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:32,208
ON THE ROAD TO THE CAPITAL.

427
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,916
- HAVE SOME PERSPECTIVE.
WE ONLY LOST A DAY OF TRAVEL.

428
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,708
YOU ACT LIKE WE JUST GOT OUT
OF PRISON OR SOMETHING.

429
00:21:36,791 --> 00:21:38,625
- HEY, SHUT UP. IT MIGHT
HAVE ONLY BEEN ONE DAY,

430
00:21:38,708 --> 00:21:40,083
BUT IT WAS A LONG ONE!

431
00:21:40,166 --> 00:21:41,583
- WELL WE'RE NOT GOING TO
MAKE UP FOR IT BY DAWDLING,

432
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:43,791
NOW ARE WE? COME ALONG.

433
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:45,916
- YOU'RE NOT LEADING.

434
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:49,416
- WHY IS HE IN SUCH A HURRY
ALL OF A SUDDEN? THAT'S ODD.

435
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,541
- WE'RE NOT GOING TO REACH
THE CAPITAL ANY MORE QUICKLY

436
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:52,916
BY DISCUSSING OUR PACE.

437
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,583
- OH, LIKE YOU'RE ONE TO TALK.

438
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:56,666
- ( both laugh )

439
00:21:58,083 --> 00:22:01,875
- OH, WELL, WAIT UP, GUYS.

440
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:08,291
- ( theme song playing )

441
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,708
- ( singing in Japanese )

442
